      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While St. John's Wort can help alleviate mild depression, taking it with sertraline may not be ideal. Sertraline is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI), and St. John's Wort can interact with this medication by decreasing its effectiveness or causing severe serotonin syndrome. It's best to consult your doctor or a pharmacist before taking St. John's Wort with your prescribed medication, especially during finals week.",
